fashionably dressed race goers at the opening of 
the fourday royal ascot meet sweltered in 88degree heat and more 
than 50 collapsed firstaid workers reported 
weve been very very busy said patricia gates of the st 
john ambulance brigades volunteer corps she said most of the 
victims on tuesday suffered mild sunstroke or fainted 
it was the hottest june day in 13 years and the champagne stalls 
were busy the price of a bottle ranged from 33 to 70 
half a cold lobster cost 1550 a serving of salmon 1240 and 
strawberries and clotted cream 310 
