<TEXT>
attorney general dick thornburghs plan to 
place the nations elite corps of organized crimefighting 
prosecutors under control of us attorneys is coming under fire 
from former leaders of the unit 
its impractical it just wont work philadelphia attorney 
peter f vaira said tuesday at a hearing of the house subcommittee 
on criminal justice 
under thornburghs plan prosecutors who are members of the 
20yearold organized crime strike force would no longer report to 
the justice departments criminal division instead they would be 
controlled by the politically appointed us attorneys in the cities 
were they are based 
thornburgh says the idea would end turf battles between the 
strike force and the us attorneys his critics say the elite 
force which has chalked up impressive victories in the war against 
the mob would soon vanish 
i guarantee you three years from now it will take the fbi to 
find the strike forces said vaira a former strike force chief in 
chicago and phildelphia who also was us attorney in philadelphia 
and briefly headed the presidents commission on organized crime 
