began in march 1985 
the negotiations are on the strategic arms reduction treaty 
intended to cut longrange nuclear forces and space and defense 
issues the talks are aimed at reducing us and soviet longrange 
bombers missiles and nuclear submarines by 30 percent to 50 percent 
this round due to last about six weeks began monday with a 
meeting of the two delegation heads 
both burt and nazarkin made plain that their public positions 
