bans on drilling in offshore areas in northern and southern 
california environmental considerations linked to drilling in those 
areas is under review by a task force appointed last march by 
president bush it is due to report to him next january 
the subcommittee also voted to continue for another year existing 
bans on oil drilling in areas off southern floria and to withhold 
for one year plans for selling exploration leases in a midatlantic 
area stretching from maryland to rhode island 
