added althaus who was working to avoid a partyline vote in his own 
race since democratic mayors outnumber republicans 
the race was for the job of chairman of the conferences advisory 
committee it carries an unglamorous title but the job is third on 
the groups leadership ladder and means the winner will be scheduled 
to assume the post of president of the conference and leading 
spokesman for the nations mayors in 1991 
