<TEXT>
thai jet fighters dropped bombs 
and helicopterborne us infantrymen swooped down on imaginary 
enemies wednesday in the climax to this years joint war games 
about 400 us troops and a like number of thai soldiers took 
part in a day of live fire exercises in hilly forested countryside 
about 200 miles northwest of bangkok 
the scenario in the cobra gold 89 war games called for the 
two sides to resist an enemy push and launch a counterattack with 
the support of tanks artillery and air strikes 
a company from the 3rd brigade of the us 25th infantry division 
was flown into attack position while jets and helicopter gunships 
provided support 
both sides flew supersonic f16 fighters which thailand has 
acquired from the united states two thai air force f5 warplanes 
dropped 500pound bombs on a hillside 
the exercise was watched by military attaches from the region and 
brig gen mya thien of burma 
burmese troops have recently intruded and fired weapons into 
thailand while fighting karen rebels the fighting continues along 
the frontier just west of where the games were staged 
cobra gold 89 the eighth in this annual series began june 
3 and has involved 6000 thai troops and 3200 us personnel 
including 2000 from the hawaiibased us 25th infantry division 
the united states which based thousands of troops in thailand 
during the vietnam war is the countrys key western ally 
