<TEXT>
four people including a fatherdaughter team of 
lawyers ran a babyselling scheme that bilked 100 couples of 
500000 authorities charged 
only 50 couples got babies state attorney general robert abrams 
said tuesday some others who had paid up to 16000 got neither a 
child nor a refund after being told the mother miscarried or changed 
her mind he said 
authorities said the brokers actually were selling the babies to 
the highest bidder doing business in such places as the parking lot 
of an international house of pancakes 
the mothers mostly unwed teenagers from rural areas were lured 
through ads in the star a supermarket tabloid and offered help 
with adoption counseling free medical care and financial support 
the adoptive couples were middleclass people from urban areas in 
21 states and canada 
seymour fenichel and his daughter deborah fenichel greenspan 
both lawyers and harriet and lawrence lauer all of new york city 
were indicted on 144 counts 
the four pleaded innocent tuesday to charges of grand larceny 
conspiracy fraud perjury filing false documents and making false 
statements by illegally operating child haven of northeastern 
pennsylvania a private adoption agency 
abrams said neither the mothers who gave up their children nor 
the adoptive parents face charges officials also said it was 
unlikely the mothers would try to get the children back 
partly because the four defendants used a legitimate social 
worker to process the adoption cases through the courts the 
attorney general said he felt the children were in good hands and 
the adoptions were not reversible 
the lauers attorney harvey baum said our clients 
involvement with adoption agencies have sprung from their own 
experiences in overcoming great obstacles in obtaining their own 
children in adoption 
their actions were always generated from good intentions and to 
help others who had the same problems they had he said 
mrs lauer wrote an article for good housekeeping magazine in 
1979 about getting her younger daughter through a classified ad 
fenichel was released on 100000 bail his daughter on 2500 
the lauers were released and given two weeks to raise 10000 bail 
the most serious charge carries a maximum of seven years in 
prison and a 5000 fine or double the amount illegally gained 
abrams said he would seek restitution for the couples 
</TEXT>
