iran and the soviet union ended nearly a decade of 
icy relations wednesday when irans parliament speaker invited 
mikhail s gorbachev to visit iran and the two leaders agreed on 
wide economic cooperation 
speaker hashemi rafsanjani told the soviet president that 
iranians hold him in high esteem and look forward to meeting him 
the official tass news agency reported 
it said gorbachev thanked rafsanjani for the invitation and said 
frequent highlevel contacts are appropraite as relations warm no 
date was set 
only a handful of third world leaders have visited tehran since 
the 1979 islamic revolution transformed the iranian capital into a 
city known for mobs of religious fanatics shouting death to 
america death to russia 
rafsanjani and gorbachev have been meeting in the kremlin over 
two days with a number of their colleagues tass said they will sign 
several agreements before rafsanjani leaves moscow 
among them are a promise to be good neighbors on their 1550mile 
border and an agreement on joint projects in 15 areas of the 
economy including nuclear energy gas processing and space 
the level of relations which may extend to putting an iranian on 
board a soviet spaceship marks a dramatic turnaround earlier this 
decade the soviet union was supplying weapons for iraq to fight 
iran and ayatollah ruhollah khomeinis fundamentalist regime was 
banning irans communist party 
in contrast tass quoted rafsanjani as saying wednesday i have 
been in moscow less than 24 hours yet already i feel almost at 
home 
