which 737400s were forced to make emergency landings because fan 
blades broke in their cfm 563c engines 
the engines are manufactured by cfm international a joint 
venture between snecma of france and general electric of the united 
states 
britains aviation authority imposed power cuts of 1500 pounds 
of thrust on the cfm 563c engines effectively converting them to a 
previous generation of that make 
the planes will be allowed a maximum thrust of 22000 pounds the 
same as the previous cfm 563b which had 6 million hours of 
reliable service 
airlines were also ordered to replace the engines fan blades and 
discs regular visual inspections of fan blades and the front face 
of the engine discs will also be required a spokesman for the 
british authority said 
