<TEXT>
a group of semiconductor companies 
today announced the formation of a manufacturing corporation that 
expects to raise more than 1 billion over several years to boost 
us production of memory chips 
the plan which sets up a corporation named us memories inc 
calls for the venture to be funded by microchip makers and their 
major customers 
companies which contributed seed money to form the 
corporation include advanced micro devices inc digital equipment 
corp hewlettpackard co international business machines corp 
intel corp lsi logic corp and national semiconductor 
the time is right for a collective memory manufacturing venture 
in the united states to improve americas market position in what is 
truly a critical technology said sanford l kane president and 
chief executive officer of the newly formed corporation and a former 
vice president at ibm 
the venture is aimed at lessening the dependence on japan for 
drams the dynamic random access memory chips that are important to 
computers consumer electronics and advanced military hardware 
us companies which once led the dram business account for 
about 15 percent of the 12 billion north american market 
another chip consortium called sematech researches new 
manufacturing technologies but cannot build commercial products it 
is funded with 100 million annually from the defense department and 
an equal amount from 14 us chipmakers 
us memories is expected to begin by setting up a highvolume 
plant to make a new generation of dram that can store 4 million bits 
of information 
japanese companies are just beginning to ship samples of the 
fourmegabit varieties that offer four times the storage of the 
onemegabit chips often found in personal computers 
the semiconductor industry association has been organizing the 
consortium 
any consortium that brings together us electronics companies 
to further our global advantage is a step in the right direction 
said william krause chairman of the american electronics 
association i find this to be a very positive step 
