<TEXT>
japanese businessmen cautiously are returning to 
china hoping to resume the business that they long have conducted 
in that market while remaining wary of another outbreak of unrest 
foreign minister hiroshi mitsuzuka has criticized businessmen for 
returning too quickly saying they invited charges that they are 
trying to make money like a thief at a fire but the government 
has not formally asked firms to refrain from business 
japan has been more cautious in its criticism of china than the 
united states which is pushing for the suspension of all new world 
bank loans to protest the chinese governments bloody suppression of 
prodemocracy demonstrations two weeks ago 
for the time being the japanese government is not considering 
