dish of rice beef and vegetables 
halls 50 employees ship 80000 pounds of cooked beef a month to 
japan the maximum allowed under a governmentset quota the beef 
cooked and packed in sixpound pouches is used in various nitto 
products 
pro foods also ships 40000 pounds of frozen beefrice a month 
packed in plastic pouches that can be heated in boiling water or 
microwave ovens 
to assure the authenticity of the dish the rice is steamed in a 
japanese rice cooker resembling a large safe complete with a wheel 
to bolt it shut another japanese machine keeps the beef slices to a 
thickness of between 15 and 25 millimeters a tolerance specified 
by nitto 
a third japanese machine known as a nitrogen tunnel cools the 
beefrice pouches to minus10 degrees fahrenheit the blast of 
nitrogen keeps the rice from clumping when heated and served 
we send it to small restaurants and cafeterias the people in 
the back know it was made in savannah ga but not the customers 
said saga 
saga who spent six years developing frozen and canned foods in 
nittos yamagata headquarters has been assigned permanently to 
savannah he is one of two japanese quality control consultants at 
pro foods nitto sends a new assistant every three months 
japanese consumers eat rice about three times a day but have to 
pay about five times more than their american counterparts said 
saga to protect growers the japanese government bars imports of 
cheaper foreign rice but permits foods containing rice 
beef the secondmost popular meat in japan after fish must be 
imported because the japanese cannot produce enough to meet demand 
said hall as a result the wholesale price of beef is 8 to 12 a 
pound in japan compared to about 350 a pound for prime filet 
mignon at american grocery stores he said 
saga is developing additional products for pro foods to export 
his countrymen like italian food but probably would not enjoy chili 
and tacos he said 
saga also doesnt see a future for halls catfish gumbo because 
in japanese mythology catfish are thought to cause earthquakes 
there are many catfish in japan but they are never eaten 
saga said 
hall believes there are many untapped opportunities for small 
companies such as ramph that want to sell to the japanese but the 
firms will have to supply products that meet their needs and 
specifications 
the future is in small ventures hall said there are 124 
million japanese living in an area the size of california they all 
eat they all sleep and they all drink the items that can be 
manufactured here to japanese specifications are just unlimited 
