elf aquitaine inc which has agreed to buy 
pennwalt corp for more than 1 billion extended its offer of 132 
per share for two weeks wednesday 
the extension was the third with aquitaine in each case saying 
more time was needed to comply with the federal trade commissions 
request for information and documents about the deal 
the french governmentcontrolled oil and chemical company said in 
a news release it expects to submit all the documents to the ftc by 
next week 
as of noontime wednesday aquitaine had acquired at least 431 
million shares of the us chemical company at the time the deal 
was announced pennwalt had about 8 million common shares 
outstanding 
the deadline which had been set for friday was extended to 5 
pm july 7 
pennwalt agreed to the purchase march 20 to thwart a hostile 
takeover attempt by centaur partners three days after the agreement 
was announced centaur ended its 110pershare offer for the 
company 
pennwalts stock closed up 137 on the new york stock exchange 
on wednesday at 12875 the extension was announced after the 
market closed 
